\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10355627 19. WAGES AND PAY }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9786180 
\par 
\par There is further reference in Regional and: postal Censorship reports to "the inadequacy" of .the increase in servicemen's pay, although there is some slight satisfaction that there is an increase it all. To quote from a writer; "What do you think of t
hem raising the soldiers' pay sixpence a day \endash  sixpence! I wonder what the people that's picking up pounds a week would say if they were given that amount rise". Comparison continues to be made between servicemen's ray and that of }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10355627 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li426\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin426\itap0\pararsid10355627 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9786180 (i)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10355627  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9786180 munition workers, and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10355627 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9786180 (ii) U.S. troops.
